    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min, turning occasionally, until they are browned all over</p><p>Meanwhile, combine the<strong> remaining chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>Henderson’s Relish</strong> and<strong> redcurrant jelly</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>dried cranberries</strong> to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the meatballs have browned, transfer them to a plate and set aside, these will finish cooking in the sauce later</p>",
      "order": 3,
