    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat, and once hot, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and stir until a sandy paste forms (if your pan is looking dry add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>)</p><p>Gradually whisk in the <strong>stock </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until slightly thickened</p>",
      "order": 4,
